Over 130 kids are taking part in the ongoing 3rd NNPC/Shell Nigeria U-12 Basketball Championship at the Sports Hall of the National Stadium, Surulere, Lagos. More than 50 games will be played by several academies from different parts of the country. Coordinator of the championship that tipped off on Monday, John Igie Adams, expressed his gratitude to NNPC, Shell and the Nigeria Basketball Federation for supporting the championship being organised by the Africa Youth Initiative on Crime Prevention ( AYICRIP).